Guys, I can guaranty you that we *can not* use google trends to retrieve any data! Especially corona related data!
Why?
1. The only way to retrieve correct data from Google trends is to use the feature called *"Include low search volume regions"*

And guess what Google's excuse is not to allow the corona related data to be used by individuals.

attachments.title: Respiratory virus shedding in exhaled breath and efficacy of face mask
attachments.text: A study of 246 individuals with seasonal respiratory virus infections randomized to wear or not wear a surgical face mask showed that masks can significantly reduce detection of coronavirus and influenza virus in exhaled breath and may help interrupt virus transmission.
